value.value: This gene is involved in the mediation of immune function.
An abnormal growth in the chest wall.
This gene is involved in catabolic polyamine metabolism and cell migration.
This gene plays a role in the induction of behavioral responses and in vasodilation.
This gene plays a role in thyroid hormone biosynthesis.
This gene plays a regulatory role in the biosynthesis of thyroid stimulating hormone.
This gene plays a role in tryptophan catabolism.
This gene is involved in sensory transduction and the biosynthesis of melanin.

Dual specificity protein phosphatase 22 (184 aa, ~22 kDa) is encoded by the human DUSP22 gene. This protein is involved in both protein dephosphorylation and the regulation of the JNK signaling pathway.
Insulin receptor-related protein (1297 aa, ~144 kDa) is encoded by the human INSRR gene. This protein plays a role in pH-mediated signaling
Early placenta insulin-like peptide (139 aa, ~15 kDa) is encoded by the human INSL4 gene. This protein plays a role in both trophoblast development and bone formation.

label.value: Anaplastic Large Cell Lymphoma, Giant Cell Rich Subtype

value.value: An anaplastic large cell lymphoma characterized by the presence of numerous giant cells.

label.value: Anaplastic Large Cell Lymphoma, Sarcomatoid Subtype

value.value: A are variant of anaplastic large cell lymphoma. It is characterized by presence of large spindle shaped cells resembling a soft tissue sarcoma.

label.value: Anaplastic Large Cell Lymphoma, Signet Ring-Like Subtype

value.value: An anaplastic large cell lymphoma, characterized by lymphoid cells with signet ring nuclei.

A short chain synthetic antigenic peptide (GILGFVFTL) derived from the influenza virus A matrix protein and presented by HLA-A2 major histocompatibility complex (MHC) class I molecules. Flu matrix peptide p58-66 stimulates the lytic functions of cytotoxic T lymphocytes (CTLs), which may result in the eradication of virus-infected or malignant tumor cells.

label.value: Neoplastic Small to Medium-Sized T-Lymphocyte with Irregular Nucleus

value.value: An herb obtained from the plant Eugenia jambolana.  Jambul seeds and fruits have important carminative and astringent properties and may reduce blood sugar levels.  This agent contains glucosides, jamboline and ellagic acid which may check the conversion of starch into sugar.  Jambul may have chemoprotective and chemopreventive effects. (NCI04)

An herb obtained from the plant Harpagophytum procumbens.  Devil's claw has been used as a tonic, as a hypoglycemic, to cleanse the lymph system, and in the treatment of arthritis, rheumatism, and skin cancer.  This agent may have anti-inflammatory and analgesic properties, possibly due to the presence of antioxidants, phenols, tannins, triterpenoids and volatile oils. (NCI04)
A white blood cell, differentiated in the thymus, activated by an antigen that causes the cell to preferentially migrate to the skin.

A white blood cell that is derived from a lymphocyte stem cell matured in the thymus and characterized by a CD8 marker on the surface and an antigen-specific T cell receptor which recognizes antigens in the context of MHC class I.
A pathologic process that affects the skin and is confined to a specific area.
A small (less than 5-10 mm) elevation of skin that is non-suppurative.
A microscopic finding indicating the presence of cells with sarcomatoid, usually spindle cell differentiation in a tumor sample.
A clinical finding that refers to the spread or absence of lymphoid cancer in anatomic sites or systems other than the original lymph node site of growth.
An elaboration of the sequence of events that play a role in organismal defense responses.
A representation of the sequence of biological or biochemical events that are involved in the regulation of or result in apoptosis.
O hydroxycinnamic acid. Pleasant smelling compound found in many plants and released on wilting. Has anticoagulant activity by competing with Vitamin K.
Abnormal fluid filled sac within the kidney, either acquired or congenital.
A representation of the sequence of biological or biochemical events that are involved in the regulation of the cell cycle.
A sequence of biological or biochemical events that are manifest during the course of a disease.
A sequence of biological or biochemical events that result in the catabolism of large molecules or polymers.
An elaboration of the known steps and interactions required to allow cell movement.
A sequence of biological or biochemical events that are involved in embryological or cellular development.
A sequence of biological or biochemical events that play a role in DNA repair.

An inorganic compound containing aluminum.  Used in various immunologic preparations to improve immunogenicity, aluminum hydroxide adjuvant consists of aluminum hydroxide gel in a saline solution.  In vaccines, this agent binds to the protein conjugate, resulting in improved antigen processing by the immune system. (NCI04)
